/*
 * This example demonstrates how to send raw JSON as a string payload via [http.put].
 *
 * [http.put]
 * - Targets https://httpbin.org/put for echo testing.
 *
 * [payload]
 * - Provided as a raw JSON string to simulate a static payload structure.
 * - Useful when dealing with hand-crafted or preformatted JSON bodies.
 */
http.put:"https://httpbin.org/put"
   payload:"{ \"product_id\": 202, \"name\": \"Super Widget\", \"stock\": 150 }"
